## Behavioral Pattern Analysis Module
This module processes location events in batch (daily) and real-time streams using Apache Kafka for ingestion and Apache Spark for analytics. It computes indicators over rolling 7-day windows.

### Analysis Logic
- **Social Isolation**: Query co-located students during "social hours" (e.g., 18:00-02:00 weekdays, all day weekends). Flag if average daily co-locations < 2 for >80% of hours.
- **Attendance Drop**: Compare actual class building entries to scheduled classes. Flag if attendance rate drops >30% from baseline (computed as 4-week moving average).
- **Counseling Center Visits**: Count entries to counseling building ID. Flag if >3 visits in a week (configurable threshold).
- **Conduct Association**: Cross-reference co-located students with conductStatus=true. Flag if >5 hours/week co-located with such students.
- **Irregular Sleep**: Infer from dorm entry/exit. Compute sleep duration as time between last exit (pre-06:00) and first entry (post-20:00). Flag if average <6 hours or variance >2 hours over 7 days.

